 "text": "\nAfter two months of perfect production, my NFS server running FreeBSD 3.2\nstarted to crash unexpectedly. I changed the complete hardware of the CPU\n(mainboard, memory, ethernet card (fxp0)) and it still crashed. I updated\nto FreeBSD 3.3 (changing the system disk as well). It crashed several other \ntimes. I noticed at this time that it always paniced in ip_reass ou fxp \ndriver. So I changed the fxp card for a brand new DIGITAL DE500, namely de \ndriver. And it kept on crashing, with different place of crash in the code \nbut still in the networking part of the kernel. Please find enclosed 2 \nuuencoded traces from kgdb run on the 2 vmcore I managed to get yesterday \nand today.\n\nbegin 644 typescript\nM4V-R:7!T('-T87)T960@;VX@1G)I(%-E\u003c\" R-\" Q.#HR-SHU-R Q.3DY\"@HC\nM(\u0026=D8B M:PI'3E4@9V1B(#0N,3@*0V]P\u003e7)I9VAT(#$Y.3@@1G)E92!3;V9T\nM=V%R92!\u0026;W5N9\u0026%T:6]N+\"!);F,N\"D=$0B!I\u003cR!F\u003cF5E('-O9G1W87)E+\"!C\nM;W9E\u003cF5D(\u0026)Y('1H92!'3E4@1V5N97)A;\"!0=6)L:6,@3\u0026EC96YS92P@86YD\nM('EO=2!A\u003cF4*=V5L8V]M92!T;R!C:\u0026%N9V4@:70@86YD+V]R(\u00261I\u003cW1R:6)U\nM=\u00264@8V]P:65S(\u0026]F(\u0026ET('5N9\u00265R(\u0026-E\u003cG1A:6X@8V]N9\u0026ET:6]N\u003cRX*5'EP\nM92 B\u003cVAO=R!C;W!Y:6YG(B!T;R!S964@=\u0026AE(\u0026-O;F1I=\u0026EO;G,N\"E1H97)E\nM(\u0026ES(\u0026%B\u003cV]L=71E;'D@;F\\@=V%R\u003cF%N='D@9F]R($=$0BX@(%1Y\u003c\u00264@(G-H\nM;W\u003c@=V%R\u003cF%N='DB(\u00269O\u003cB!D971A:6QS+@I4:\u0026ES($=$0B!W87,@8V]N9FEG\nM=7)E9\"!A\u003cR B:3,X-BUU;FMN;W=N+69R965B\u003cV0B+@HH:V=D8BD@\u003cWEM8F]L\nM+69I;\u00264@:V5R;F5L+F1E8G5G\"E)E861I;F\u003c@\u003cWEM8F]L\u003cR!F\u003cF]M(\u0026ME\u003cFYE\nM;\"YD96)U9RXN+F1O;F4N\"BAK9V1B*2!E\u003e\u00265C+69I;\u00264@+W9A\u003cB]C\u003cF%S:\"]K\nM97)N96PN,0HH:V=D8BD@8V]R92UF:6QE(\"]V87(O8W)A\u003cV@O=FUC;W)E+C$*\nM261L95!41\" R.#8S,3 T\"FEN:71I86P@\u003c\u0026-B(\u0026%T(#(T9\u00268Y. IP86YI8W-T\nM\u003cCH@9G)O;2!D96)U9V=E\u003c@IP86YI8R!M97-S86=E\u003cSH*+2TM\"D9A=\u0026%L('1R\nM87 